Flooding has been reported in parts of Johannesburg north, with the downpours expected to spread to other parts of Gauteng. JOHANNESBURG - The South African Weather Service has issued a warning for severe thunderstorms across Gauteng on Tuesday afternoon.Flooding has been reported in parts of Johannesburg north, with the downpours expected to spread to other parts of the province later this afternoon and then into the evening.Forecaster Mkhushulwa Msimang said: We expect thunderstorms to be around the Gauteng province during the course of this afternoon into midnight and tomorrow the thunderstorms might start late in the morning. (Edited by Winnie Theletsane)